# Practice Section Content

Timed retrieval drills organised by grammatical structure. The practice surface is the production-skill engine of the app — Skill Acquisition Theory (DeKeyser) procedural-fluency training. Drills push learners from explicit knowledge → procedural skill → automatisation.

## Route Structure

```
/practice                                       Section landing — drill registry
/practice/articles/{paradigm,context,…}         Article paradigm + per-case article drills
/practice/articles/noun-{genders,target,owner}  Per-case noun drills
/practice/adjectives/{agreement,…-target,…-owner}  Per-case adjective agreement drills
/practice/nominal/{phrase-doer,phrase-target,phrase-owner}  Phrase-builder capstones
/practice/nominal/{all-nouns,all-adjectives}    DB-driven cross-case review drills
/practice/pronouns/{object,possessives}         Pronoun paradigms
/practice/verbs/{present,conjugation-endings,…} Verb drills
/practice/blocks/{chunks,numbers,days-of-week}  Building blocks
```

## Landing Page

<route path="/practice">
<purpose>Drill registry hub — surfaces every drill grouped by word class + case-phase</purpose>
<file>src/routes/practice/index.tsx</file>
<source-of-truth>src/routes/practice/drills.ts — DRILLS array, GROUP_META, GROUP_ORDER</source-of-truth>
<displays>
- Four top-level sections rendered in `GROUP_ORDER`:
  - **Articles, nouns & adjectives** (group: nominal)
  - **Pronouns** (group: pronouns)
  - **Verbs** (group: verbs)
  - **Building blocks** (group: blocks)
- Each section's drills can be tagged with a `phase` field. Consecutive drills sharing a phase render under a phase sub-header.
- Phase headers carry colour accent + left border via `PHASE_TINT`:
  - **Doer** → ocean (nominative)
  - **Target** → terracotta (accusative)
  - **Owner** → olive (genitive)
  - **Present** / **Past** / **Commands** → no tint (verbs)
  - **Review** → muted neutral (cross-case mixed drills)
- Drills without a phase render as ungrouped rows.
</displays>
</route>

## Section: Articles, nouns & adjectives

Case is the primary axis. Each case-phase contains four drill types: Article → Noun → Adjective → Phrase. A Review tier at the end mixes cases.

```
DOER (ocean)
  Article (Doer)         → ο · η · το · οι · τα           hand-curated, 6 forms
  Noun (Doer)            → ο φίλος · η μέρα · το σπίτι     hand-curated, 30 nouns
  Adjective agreement    → καλός · καλή · καλό            hand-curated, 30 forms
  Doer phrase            → ο καλός φίλος                  hand-curated capstone

TARGET (terracotta)
  Article (Target)       → τον · τη · το · τους · τις · τα
  Noun (Target)          → τον φίλο · τη μέρα · το σπίτι
  Adjective (Target)     → καλό · καλή · καλό
  Target phrase          → τον καλό φίλο                  capstone

OWNER (olive)
  Article (Owner)        → του · της · του · των
  Noun (Owner)           → του φίλου · της μέρας · του σπιτιού
  Adjective (Owner)      → καλού · καλής · καλού
  Owner phrase           → του καλού φίλου                capstone

REVIEW (neutral)
  All articles           → existing 18-form DimensionalDrill
  All nouns              → DB-driven, queries vocabulary + nominal_forms
  All adjectives         → DB-driven, queries vocabulary + nominal_forms
  All article + noun     → server-driven mixed-case article+noun pairs
```

<engine-notes>
- Hand-curated drills use `SimpleListDrill` engine with `colorTheme` matching the case (ocean/terracotta/olive).
- Phrase capstones use `SimpleListDrill` with multi-word Greek strings; `matchPhonetic` accepts whitespace-separated input.
- DB-driven review drills (`all-nouns`, `all-adjectives`) have route-level loaders that query `nominal_forms` via `getNominalFormsForDrill`, build `DrillQuestion[]`, pass to `VocabDrillPage` via `initialQuestions` prop.
</engine-notes>

## Section: Pronouns

Function-word grids — kept separate from Nominal section because the cognitive task is paradigm recall, not case morphology applied to semantic content.

- Object pronouns: με, σε, τον, την, μας, σας…
- Possessives: μου, σου, του, της, μας…

Both use `DimensionalDrill` engine.

## Section: Verbs

Tense as primary axis. Phase headers: Present / Past / Commands.

```
PRESENT
  Basic verbs · Conjugations · Irregular verbs · είμαι · present

PAST
  Conjugations · Irregular verbs · είμαι · past · Past ↔ present

COMMANDS
  Imperatives
```

Past-tense conjugation drill is server-driven (queries verb_conjugations). Other verb drills are hand-curated SimpleListDrill content.

## Section: Building blocks

Heterogeneous grab-bag. Currently no phase structure.

- Survival phrases · Numbers · Days & time

## Educational principle

Each phase mirrors the production-skill operation a learner performs at speed:
- Bare form (Article) — function-word retrieval
- Single-class application (Noun, Adjective) — morphology
- Phrase integration (Phrase capstone) — full noun-phrase production

Asymmetric content reflects honest priority. Owner has fewer drills than Doer because Owner forms appear less in casual speech. Don't symmetrise where frequency disagrees.

## Data sources

- **Hand-curated drill content**: lives inside each drill file's `tsx` (e.g. `articles/article-doer.tsx`).
- **Vocabulary + cases**: seeded into `vocabulary` + `nominal_forms` via `src/scripts/seed.ts`. Enrichment in `noun-seed-enrichment.ts` calls `declineNoun` to populate all (case × number) cells; `adjective-seed-enrichment.ts` calls `declineAdjective` for (case × number × gender) cells.
- **Verb conjugations**: seeded inside the same `seed.ts` pipeline (calls `seedVerbConjugations()` at the end).

See `src/db.server/CLAUDE.md` for query patterns.
